phrases: It is nice to meet you all.
This is Hattori, from the Weekly Shounen Jack editing department.
I am here today to represent Ashirogi Mutou, the authors of the original work.
Please do a good job with the Reversi anime.
Now then, let us introduce the cast.
As soon as I reach my goals, it all falls through again
We met after such a long time
Has the mood changed for us?
It seemed like more fun back then
Do not stop screaming, do not stop struggling
You have done enough for others
I still, still have something I have not told you yet
Beyond each of my dreams lies yet another dream
It Will be an emotional moment for me.
I was with Ashirogi for only three years, but we went through a lot of things together.
By the way, they have not gone to a recording session or anything, have they?
They do not want to do anything like that until the show actually airs.
It is just like Mashiro to do that.
He is stubborn, you might say.
Nah, Azuki's a handful as well.
Though she may seem meek on the outside.
So they are birds of a feather, then.
I will be so jittery until then!
You already saw it at the private showing.
It is the TV broadcast I am nervous about!
Mashiro, you are nervous too, right?
Saikou's nervous in a different way, right?
After Reversi's anime is broadcast tomorrow, I am going to go see Azuki.
Miho never said anything about that!
Oh, so that is why the assistants are off tomorrow.
I will officially propose to her.
But her response is 100 guaranteed to be yes already,
so there is really no reason for you to be nervous.
The dream that they encouraged each other to pursue, never meeting face-to-face, has finally been achieved.
So going to see her is a big deal, you know?
That is why he is going to propose to her then.
There is no way he would not be nervous.
So it will be like the most important day in Mashiro Moritaka's life, right?
What is up with you today?
You seem very up-front about this.
It is because I am thankful to you.
I would like to shake your hand.
Are you trying to grab the hand of a married woman?
Kaya, I have been thinking of telling you this one day, and it seems like now's the time.
The pen name you gave us, Ashirogi Mutou, always manages to encourage me.
I think Azuki must feel the same way.
So even I was of some use!
You did all the housework here and even helped us out with our work sometimes!
And besides, Mashiro, Akito and Miho made me happy!
I should be the one thanking you!
You two must have some guy things you would like to talk about.
We do not even have any guy things to talk about anyway.
We will just keep going on as we are.
The Reversi anime will begin tomorrow.
When the anime airs, Mashiro will come to see me.
He is going to ask for us to give you away?
I have not even prepared anything!
If that were the case, then he would have told you beforehand.
Then I suppose it is for a date.
It is your first date, is not it?
You promised each other that you would get married if you each achieved your dreams,
and tried your best without even seeing each other.
I am very happy for you.
So when were you going to tell me that you are the number one author in Jack?
Actually, right now I do not have a weekly series.
So you cannot really say that my current number one” status is the real thing.
I will wait a little longer, then.
Come and tell me when you get there.
manga artist as soon as possible!
What you wanted to do, what you could not do...
I will make it all a reality.
Thou shalt not enter without warning.
Hey, you seem kind of down.
We just got news that GIRI is 2nd in the early rankings.
Oh, that is great, is not it?
It is not good at all.
There is too much of a gap between us and Zombie Gun in 1st.
On the other hand, the gap between GIRI in 2nd and +NATURAL in 5th is practically nil.
At this rate, we are just here to make Niizuma look good.
It is been in first place the entire time since Reversi ended!
It was such a shame about Reversi.
I mean, the anime just started today.
We are going to change Jack.
Master Niizuma and Ashirogi have come up with one way of doing it.
What would it look like if I did not follow up with my own?
You are in 8th in the early rankings this week.
Do not you think you have been lacking your usual negativity lately?
That is because I have never been happier!
He is losing his energy source.
What happened to my Become a Super Manga Artist plan?
I have already lost ten kilos.
I have been thinking about it, of course!
I thought it is about time we entered the plan's second stage.
Never mind the plan; I forgot he even existed.
Well then, Yuri and I are going to plan our wedding while we watch Ashirogi's anime!
For now, just drop another 40 kilos.
You will probably be number one in the final ranking at this rate.
That will make it 30 weeks in a row!
Cannot get excited without Ashirogi around?
Until Ashirogi returns, I will not lose to anybody.
I want to see the moment their dreams come true.
It has not started yet, has it?
But I will not make it in time!
If I miss the beginning, it will be your fault, Mom!
My dream with Mashiro will be fulfilled soon.
The dream from our third year of middle school.
Even though we have the same goal...
Our ways of thinking are just too different.
We just cannot get around it.
Let Us begin the game that will destroy humanity!
In three years, they will surpass Niizuma Eiji.
So you are watching it here?
Do not want to make the other editors uncomfortable?
I think Kawaguchi would be happy.
Not just anyone can do that.
This world where people cannot even follow rules...
There is no way I can change it.
There are some parts of yesterday's math homework that I do not understand.
From now on, each student will be allotted 20 points,
and with each violation of the rules,
points will be deducted according to the severity of the transgression.
And if your points fall to zero, you will be expelled.
It is obvious that one should follow the rules.
I see no problem with this.
If you do not like it, you can quit.
Yamada, you are the the student council president!
If I have this kind of power, then changing the world is not impossible anymore!
then I cannot pass it up.
I will make a contract with you.
Those who sign a contract with a demon can infect others with their ideology.
Those who sign a contract with a demon can infect others with their ideology.
Aiba Satoru Futanomiya Sora Minadori Naho
Nakatani Susumu Kanade Yuuichi Azuki Miho
Aiba Satoru Futanomiya Sora Minadori Naho
Nakatani Susumu Kanade Yuuichi Azuki Miho
All that is left now is for him to propose.
I-I am nervous all of a sudden now.
It was good, was not it, Sis?
I am in front of your house right now.
It does not really suit you, though.
But it is fine this way.
Once I become a first-rate manga artist,
I am going to propose to Haruno.
And I will come pick her up in a high-class foreign ca
No seat is too good for Haruno.
When I propose, we will go to that
And I will come pick her up in a high-class foreign car while I am at it!
I will make sure she sits next to me in style.
The happiest time of my life was in middle school
when Haruno and I were seated next to each other.
Seeing you makes my heart beat fast, but I am still calm.
It just feels so right to have you sitting next to me.
During middle school, I was at my happiest when my desk was lined up with yours.
I-I felt the same way, too.
Whenever you sat next to me, I mean.
You were always on my right side.
I am going to propose to Haruno and create that space with her again.
That is why you came in a foreign car...
This was actually one of my uncle'sone of Kawaguchi Tarou's dreams.
He wrote in his diary that he would come visit the girl he loved in a high-class foreign car.
He did not get to do it, though.
So I wanted to fulfill that dream for him, no matter what.
It worked out perfectly that the driver's side is on the left.
So that you could be on my right.
That is just like you, Mashiro.
We will be moving, so please put on your seatbelt.
The girl that Mashiro's uncle wanted to visit was probably...
But their relationship never got past an exchange of letters.
If we go to a place that holds memories for us,
then I am sure that the right words of the proposal will come naturally.
Honest words for honest people like us.
My mom likes it, and keeps talking about moving back here one day.
Mashiro, why did you bring us here?
This is the place where we first spoke to each other.
I will draw the art, and he will write the story.
I know you can do it!
The second time we spoke to each other was also here.
It was the day we graduated.
It is a place filled with memories for us.
This is the same situation I was in on our graduation day!
That day, I just stood there and could not say anything!
I am not a middle schooler anymore!
Uncle, the right words are not coming naturally to me!
It is been exactly ten years since we first spoke to each other here.
You have not changed at all, Mashiro.
You are the same as you were ten years ago.
Even though you have become an adult, fulfilled your dream,
and almost everything around you kept changing,
you have not changed one bit, Mashiro.
I am glad you have not.
Honest words for honest people like us.
Our dream was for our manga to become an anime, and for you to voice its heroine.
Now that we have made that dream a reality, will you marry me?
I will be by your side from now on.
Yoshida, you are crying too much.
I am talking about a new manga that is even better than +NATURAL!
Because you have just taken over,
I expect you to have at least one or two ideas prepared
I have three, four or five new ideas!
An offer to make Seigi no Mikata into a movie!
We will have to work out all the details, but the higher-ups are listening!
I will submit this to the serialization committee, then.
I will do my best to live up to Hattori's standards!
PCP has been getting more and more interesting lately.
Have you gotten used to your new house yet?
Well, that house is too big for just the two of them.
It is no wonder they cannot relax.
Do you just have nothing to talk about with your wife?
I am really glad your dream was fulfilled.
Making a living off of manga is what makes us manga authors.
Until we can manage that, we are just gamblers.
That is what Kawaguchi Tarou said.
Then I will read this new work of yours very carefully.
If we get serialized, we will have your wedding ceremony, right?
My uncle never told me to become a manga artist.
I am drawing manga because I want to.
A dream is not something that someone tells you to go for.
It is something you fulfill of your own will.
The Bakuman anime is now over.
What about your and Azuki's wedding ceremony?
A-As if we would show that!
Thanks for supporting us until now, everyone.
We will keep chasing our dreams!
